cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CE 

This paper is about predicting click-through and conversion rates for bidding in online advertising auctions, which is a problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG). The paper also discusses the use of cost-sensitive learning, which is a common technique in data science (DS) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper proposes a new cost weighting scheme to optimize the Utility metric, which is a measure of advertiser profit and therefore related to computational economics (CE).
